This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on June 2, 2010. The memorandum is titled "Suspension of Limitations Under the Jerusalem Embassy Act" and it addresses the Jerusalem Embassy Act of 1995. 

In the memorandum, President Obama states that he is suspending the limitations set forth in sections 3(b) and 7(b) of the Act for a period of 6 months. He justifies this action by claiming that it is necessary to protect the national security interests of the United States. The memorandum directs the Secretary of State to transmit this determination to Congress, along with a report, and to publish the determination in the Federal Register. The suspension will take effect after the transmission of the determination and report to Congress.